    <h3 class="copy-heading text-center orange">For Art Collectors</h3>

    <h4>1. Is buying art on ArtCaring secure?</h4>
      <p class="indent">All of our transactions are handled through <a href=https://stripe.com/ target="_blank">Stripe</a>. They offer the most secure way of making a credit card purchase online. We decided to use Stripe because of their built-in, compliant security, and we don't even see your credit card information this way.</p><br>

    <h4>2. What happens after I make a purchase?</h4>
      <p class="indent">The artist will be immediately notified of your purchase and we will stay in touch with them to make sure they can get your Artwork shipped off to you as soon as possible.</p><br>

    <h4>3. What happens if I receive the art and it's not as described, or not what I had hoped?</h4>
      <p class="indent">You have 7 business days to accept the art, once you've received it physically. When you make your purchase, the money is held in escrow until your acceptance of the art. Essentially, you receive the art and have some time to approve of it before finalizing the transaction. We will follow up with you via email once the art has arrived to make sure it arrive safely.</p><br>

    <h4>4. What happens if I receive the art and it's damaged?</h4>
      <p class="indent">Please <%= link_to "Contact Us", new_message_path %> immediately, and the artist as well. The artist is responsible for insuring the art during shipment, and your money is completely refundable. But we need to be notified as soon as possible so that we can take care of insurance claims on the damaged goods in coordination with the artist. We will help you through the process should this happen, so don't worry!</p><br>

    <h4>5. Can I contact the Patient I'm helping?</h4>
      <p class="indent">A great question! If you would like to send well wishes or a note to the Patient you're helping, let us know and we'll forward their mailing address to you. You may also contact the artist you bought from and they will be able to help you.</p><br>

    <h4>6. How did ArtCaring come about?</h4>
      <p class="indent">Please read our story <%= link_to "here", welcome_about_path %>.</p><br>


    
  



